  {
    "user": "U04BQN4K3AP",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1759050400.578799",
    "client_msg_id": "45d7f100-16ef-4bfe-b2a0-50b596e3d84c",
    "text": "Nice, I've been following GToolkit for some time and was quite blown away by the demo that <@UE1JQM9HQ> showed me :slightly_smiling_face:\n\nI'd say the main difference is that Comper is primarily meant to explore existing codebases, and not re-invent programming. Ultimately I think existing programming paradigms are flawed and systems like GToolkit are paving the way forward, but I fear adoption will be slow as you will have to build an entire ecosystem around it.\n\nForgot to mention, but I worked at Mendix for a long time, where we were pioneering an enterprise-grade low-code platform. That was fun, but suffered from the same problems, a lot of incompatibility with everything that is out there.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1758990502.853019",
    "parent_user_id": "U04BQN4K3AP",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "B5WsY",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Nice, I've been following GToolkit for some time and was quite blown away by the demo that "
              },
              {
                "type": "user",
                "user_id": "UE1JQM9HQ"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " showed me "
              },
              {
                "type": "emoji",
                "name": "slightly_smiling_face",
                "unicode": "1f642"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\n\nI'd say the main difference is that Comper is primarily meant to explore existing codebases, and not re-invent programming. Ultimately I think existing programming paradigms are flawed and systems like GToolkit are paving the way forward, but I fear adoption will be slow as you will have to build an entire ecosystem around it.\n\nForgot to mention, but I worked at Mendix for a long time, where we were pioneering an enterprise-grade low-code platform. That was fun, but suffered from the same problems, a lot of incompatibility with everything that is out there."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "channel_name": "present-company",
